    {
        "client_msg_id": "06d01745-939b-4377-be33-e313f7dddd3e",
        "type": "message",
        "text": "As both someone who hired writers and was hired, paid writing assignments are definitely the way to go. The length of the writing assignment should match the work that you’re expecting the writer to do when they get hired.\n\nThere are limits of course--no need to make the writer do an entire whitepaper as a trial project. But the important thing is setting expectations and making sure the writer doesn’t feel like they were taken advantage of in the event they are not hired.",
        "user": "U016BDEQ40J",
